{"change_summary":"Consolidated milestone task-run completion onto the update path: `record_bead_completion` now mutates the existing lineage row instead of appending a second entry, `update_task_run` updates lineage plus snapshot/journal state, skipped runs have explicit `BeadSkipped`/`skipped_beads` handling, and the FS adapter now locks `task-runs.ndjson`, backfills optional metadata, sorts bead queries chronologically, and rejects ambiguous or duplicate-finalization updates.","outstanding_risks":["Task-run completion still spans lineage, snapshot, and journal writes without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between writes could leave those artifacts temporarily inconsistent until repaired."],"steps":[{"description":"Extended milestone progress and journal modeling for skipped outcomes while preserving backward compatibility for legacy task-run and snapshot data.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Refactored milestone completion so both `record_bead_completion` and `update_task_run` finalize the existing lineage row, update snapshot counters/active state, and emit the correct journal event.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Hardened the filesystem lineage adapter with advisory locking, run-id-aware disambiguation/backfill, duplicate-finalization rejection, chronological bead queries, and regression coverage for retries and skipped runs.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 65 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}